    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhenever I include one of the phrases `@if`, `@for`, or `@switch` (and possibly others) in an HTML file, no language servers attached to HTML file types will run (`:=vim.lsp.get_clients()`=`{}`).\nI have tried other servers, including 5 servers in `vscode-language-server-extracted`, `lua_ls`, and `harper_ls`, and the result is the same. Therefore, I assume this is an issue with Neovim.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config[\"test_server\"] = {\n  cmd = { \"typescript-language-server\", \"--stdio\" },\n  filetypes = { \"html\", },\n}\nvim.lsp.enable(\"test_server\")\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe language servers should run regardless of any errors that occur.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1753364724\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nvscode-language-server-extracted, lua-language-server 3.15.0, typescript-language-server 4.4.0, harper 0.59.0\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchLinux 6.16.2-arch1-1\n\n### Log file\n\nThe language servers don't run, so there is no log in the `lsp.log` file",
