            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": " \n> It is so weird that `htmlangular` and `htmldjango` are supersets of `html`, but neovim lsp cannot treat these filetypes as `html`\n\nOf course it can. But those filetypes need to be listed in the config:\n\n    filetypes = { \"html\", \"htmlangular\", \"htmldjango\" }\n\nNote that https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/3145 proposed a way to automatically support \"compound filetypes\", but for that to work, the names would need to be `html.angular` and `html.django`.",
